{{Infobox airport | name = Arly Airport | IATA = ARL | ICAO = DFER | type = Public | city-served = [[Arli National Park|Arly]] | location = {{flag|Burkina Faso}} | elevation-f = 761 | elevation-m = 232 | coordinates = {{coord|11|35|50.366|N|1|28|53.115|E|region:BF_type:airport|name=Arly Airport (Arly)|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = Burkina Faso | pushpin_label= DFER | pushpin_map_caption = Location of Arly Airport in Burkina Faso | r1-number = 04/22 | r1-length-f = 4,625 | r1-length-m = 1,300 | r1-surface = Grass | footnotes = Source: Burkina Faso AIP<ref name="ASECNA AIP">[http://www.ais-asecna.org/en/ad/ad2.htm] AIP entry retrieved 2017-05-24</ref> }}
'''Arly Airport''' {{Airport codes|ARL|DFER}} is a public use [[airport]] located near '''[[Arli National Park]]''' or '''Arly''', [[Tapoa Province]], [[Burkina Faso]]. While the runway outline is clearly visible, it appears overgrown with vegetation<ref name="Google">{{Google maps|url=https://maps.google.com/maps?ht=en&z=13&t=k&q=11.597324,1.481421+%28Arly+Airport%29|title=location of Arly Airport|accessdate=2017-05-24}}</ref> and may be unusable. However, the airfield is still listed in the official ASECNA Aeronatical Information Publication for Burkina Faso<ref name="ASECNA AIP" /> and has an official IATA 3-letter code,<ref name="IATA">[http://www.iata.org/publications/Pages/code-search.aspx] IATA code search accessed 2017-05-24</ref> though its 4-letter code does not appear to be recognised by ICAO<ref name="ICAO">[https://www.icao.int/safety/iStars/Pages/API-Data-Service.aspx] ICAO location indicator search accessed 2017-05-24</ref>
