{{refimprove|date=August 2018}}
The '''Commission on European Family Law''' (as known as '''CEFL''') was established in September 2001 and has, as its main objective, the role of working for the harmonization of [[family law]] throughout [[European law|Europe]]. The CEFL consists of approximately 26 experts in the field of family and [[comparative law]] from all [[European Union]] member states, as well as several other European countries.
== Principles == One accomplishment of the commission has been the creation of a set of common principles in the area of family law based upon research of national [[legislation]] of European states.
==External links== *[http://www.ceflonline.net/ Official site] * [http://www.ceflonline.net/Reports/Principles%20-%20English.pdf Principles of European Family Law Regarding Divorce And Maintenance Between Former Spouses] * [http://www.ceflonline.net/Reports/Principles%20PR%20English.pdf Principles of European Family Law Regarding on the Parental Responsibility]
