{{Orphan|date=August 2017}}

The family de '''l'Estoile''' (also spelled as '''l'Etoile''', '''l'Estoille''' and '''Lestoille''') was a [[French people|French]] family, whose members were noted for their activities in the [[Safavid Empire]] (1501-1736). The first known member of the family that moved to Iran was Isaac Boutet de l'Estoille (died 28 July 1667, in [[New Julfa]]). He served king [[Abbas I of Persia|Abbas I]] (r. 1588-1629) as a goldsmith, amongst others.

==Notable members==
* Isaac Boutet de l'Estoille (died 28 July 1667, New Julfa)
* Louis-Guillherme de l'Estoile (died 16 June 1701, New Julfa)
* Angela (died 1675)
* André (died 1745, New Julfa)
* Alexandre (died 1707, near [[Bandar Abbas]])
* Reine (died 1766)
* Isaac de l'Estoille

