{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Use British English|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox street | name = Devil's Gap Road | native_name = "''Escalera del Monte''" | marker_image = | image = Devil's Gap Road.jpg | caption = Devils Gap Road: the steps have been painted with the [[Union Flag]] ever since [[Gibraltar sovereignty referendum, 1967|Gibraltar's first sovereignty referendum]]. | former_names = | postal_code = | addresses = | length_m = | length_ft = | length_mi = | length_km = | length_ref = | width = | location =[[Gibraltar]] | client = | maint = | coordinates = {{coord|36.138473|-5.351123|region:GI_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | direction_a = | terminus_a = | direction_b = | terminus_b = | junction = | commissioning_date = | construction_start_date = | completion_date = | inauguration_date = <!-- {{Start date|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | demolition_date = | north = | south = | east = | west = }} '''Devil's Gap Road''' (''Escalera del Monte'' in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]) is a street in the [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]].
==Description== It lies between its junction with [[Flat Bastion Road]] in the southern direction and joins [[Baca's Passage]] in the northern direction.<ref name= "Sheriff1890">{{Cite book|last=Sherif|first=RoberrFfrenc|title= The consolidated laws of Gibraltar|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8BgTAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA82&lpg=PA82&dq=Devil%27s+Gap+Road,+Gibraltar&source=bl&ots=xuuEZfmxsY&sig=_soRFc89Kx24DWzJsBrLVD8tdcI&hl=en&sa=X&ei=I0V2UOGyOcn3igKR04HQDQ&ved=0CDIQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Devil%27s%20Gap%20Road%2C%20Gibraltar&f=false|accessdate=2 May 2013|year=1890|publisher=Stevens|pages=80–81}}</ref> This street is the quickest route by foot from the city centre to the [[Upper Rock Nature Reserve]]. The [[Footpaths of Gibraltar#Devil's Gap Footpath|Devil's Gap Footpath]] leads up from where Devil's Gap Road meets Baca's Passage and joins [[Green Lane, Gibraltar|Green Lane]] near [[Devil's Gap Battery]] in the nature reserve.<ref name=discover/>
==Painting== The street is also known as the ''Union Jack Steps'' or ''Referendum Steps'' and was originally painted in 1967 to celebrate [[Gibraltar sovereignty referendum, 1967|Gibraltar's first sovereignty referendum]] of that year. In August 2011, the steps were repainted in red, white, and blue by volunteers intent on restoring the period graffiti.<ref name=discover>{{cite web|title=City of Gibraltar (map options)|url=http://www.discovergibraltar.com/pages/mainlogo/mainfrm.htm|work=discovergibraltar.com|publisher=DiscoverGibraltar.com (Click on Town area)|accessdate=2 May 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130905140025/http://www.discovergibraltar.com/pages/mainlogo/mainfrm.htm|archivedate=5 September 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Youths Step up to Referendum Challenge|url=http://www.chronicle.gi/headlines_details.php?id=22508|accessdate=2 May 2013|newspaper=Gibraltar Chronicle|date=18 August 2011|author=Mascarenhas, Alice}}</ref>
