'''Donna Taberer''' is a British [[television producer]] and former head of entertainment at Channel 5.

==Early life==
She was born in East Sussex. She attended [[grammar school]] in [[East Sussex]].{{Citation needed|date=July 2017}}

==Career==
She began as a journalist at the age of 18, and trained on the [[National Council for the Training of Journalists|NCTJ]] course.{{Citation needed|date=July 2017}}

===BBC===
She joined the BBC in 1990 as a researcher on ''[[That's Life!]]''. She worked in factual programmes and factual entertainment as an executive producer. She oversaw the ''[[Children's Party at the Palace]]'' in 2006.{{Citation needed|date=July 2017}}

She rejoined the BBC in September 2010.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/ariel/27424005 BBC Ariel September 2014]</ref>

===BSkyB===
From 2006-09 she was in charge of commissioning entertainment on [[Sky 1]], [[Sky 2]] and Sky 3.

===Five===
In August 2009 she joined Five as their head of Entertainment,<ref name=":0" /> where she stayed for a year.

===BBC Academy===
In September 2010, Taberer joined the [[BBC Academy]]<ref name=":0">{{cite news|last1=Farber|first1=Alex|title=C5's Donna Taberer returns to BBC|url=http://www.broadcastnow.co.uk/news/people/c5s-donna-taberer-returns-to-bbc/5018719.article|accessdate=15 July 2017|work=Broadcast Now|date=September 27, 2010|language=en}}</ref> where she is head of public service partnerships;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nfts.co.uk/news/bbc-award-%C2%A3750000-scholarships-nfts-students-part-3-year-deal|title=BBC to award £750,000 in scholarships to NFTS students as part of 3 year deal {{!}} National Film and Television School|website=nfts.co.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-07-15}}</ref> the Academy includes, among other initiatives, a media training program for journalists and other experts aimed at helping to achieve gender parity on television.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Bardou|first1=Florian|title=Médias, femmes et stéréotypes : la France a un (bon) train de retard|url=https://www.observatoiredesmedias.com/2014/10/20/medias-femmes-stereotypes-france-bon-train-retard/|accessdate=15 July 2017|work=L'Observatoire des médias|date=20 October 2014}}</ref>

==See also==
* [[Richard Woolfe]], former Channel control of Five from 2009

