{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}
'''EsaBac''' is a Franco-Italian high-school [[Double degree|double degree program]], signed on February 25, 2009 by [[Ministry of Education, Universities and Research (Italy)|Italian Minister of Education]] [[Mariastella Gelmini]], and [[Ministry of National Education (France)|French Minister of National Education]] [[Xavier Darcos]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ambafrance-it.org/L-EsaBac-un-solo-esame-due-diplomi |title=Ambassade de France à Rome |last= |first= |date= |website=Ambassade de France à Rome |publisher= |access-date=April 2, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402185349/http://www.ambafrance-it.org/L-EsaBac-un-solo-esame-due-diplomi |archivedate=April 2, 2015 |df= }}</ref>
The agreement, in force since September 2010,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://institutfrancais-italia.com/fr/apprendre-le-francais/cours-en-italie/lycees-italiens-a-section-esabac|title=Lycées italiens à section Esabac|access-date=2016-06-27}}</ref> allows Italian and French students to consequently obtain two high-school degrees, [[Matura|Italian Maturità]] and [[Baccalauréat|French Baccalauréat]], just in one exam.<ref name=":0" />
== References == <references />
[[Category:School examinations]] [[Category:Secondary school qualifications]] [[Category:Education in Italy]]
