{{ESC National Year | Year = 2008 | Country = Estonia | Preselection = Eurolaul 2008 | Preselection date = February 2, 2008 | Entrant = [[Kreisiraadio]] | Song = [[Leto svet]] | SF result = ''Failed to qualify'' (18th, 8 points) | Final result = }} The [[Eurovision Song Contest 2008]] was '''Estonia's''' 14th appearance in the competition.
Estonia competed in the first semi-final on May 20, 2008. The song was not among the ten songs selected for the final, the fifth consecutive year in which Estonia did not feature in the final.
== Eurolaul 2008 ==
The Estonian national final [[Eurolaul]] was held on February 2, 2008. [[Eesti Rahvusringhääling|ERR]] invited six songwriters, one of them withdrew. Five other songs were chosen by contest.
