{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}} [[File:Peace and Love Galago 5.JPG|thumb|right|250px]] '''''Galago''''' is a [[Swedish language|Swedish]] [[comics]] and illustrations [[magazine]] published in [[Sweden]]. It specializes in [[alternative comics]], and has traditionally had a [[left wing|left-leaning]] slant.
==History and profile== ''Galago'' was created in 1979<ref name=tid>{{cite news|title=Tidningen|url=http://www.galago.se/tidningen|accessdate=29 August 2016|work=Galago|language=Swedish|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161021195442/http://www.galago.se/tidningen|archivedate=21 October 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> by Rolf Classon, Olle Berg and Kerold Klang.<ref name=cv>{{cite web|title=CV|url=http://www.olle-berg.com/cv.pdf|work=Olle Berg|accessdate=12 November 2014}}</ref> The magazine was first published by Tago Publishers<ref name=cv/> and later by Atlantic Publishing. The publisher is [[Ordfront]].<ref name="tid"/> It appears four months a year.<ref name=tid/> The headquarters is in [[Stockholm]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Kontakt|url=http://www.galago.se/kontakt|accessdate=29 August 2016|work=Galago|language=Swedish}}</ref>
The present editor (as of 2018) is [[Rojin Pertow]].
