{{unreferenced|date=March 2018}} {{Infobox film | name = Halfaouine child of the terraces | image = | alt = | caption = | border = | director = [[Férid Boughedir]] | producer = | writer = Férid Boughedir | starring = | music = | editing = | studio = | distributor = | released = 1990 | runtime = 95 minutes | country = [[Tunisia]] | language = [[Arabic]] | budget = |newspaper= | gross = }} '''Halfaouine child of the terraces''' {{ara|عصفور السطح}} is a Tunisian film made in 1990, first [[feature film]] of fiction by the director [[Ferid Boughedir]]. {{TOC limit}}
== Synopsis == In Halfaouine,a neighbourhood of [[Tunis]], young Noura, finely interpreted by the nephew of the director, is divided between several worlds: that of men in the streets, the women, with whom he can still share the [[Turkish bath|hammam]], despite his puberty approaching, and his imagination, in which he fears the transition to adult life. Boughedir paints a happy picture of Tunisian life, and illustrates the subtle and complex relationships between men and women in Tunisia. The boy discovers the pleasures of life as their family adopt a teen girl. The boy tries whenever he has a chance to see her unclothed body. After three or four attempts the boy succeeds.
== Technical details == *Director: Ferid Boughedir *Scenario: Ferid Boughedir *Photography: Georges Barsky *Sets: Taieb Jallouli *Music: Anouar Brahem *Language: Tunisian Arabic *Format: color *Genre: comedy drama
