{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}

[[File:Hans Mathisen.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Herr Nilsen Jazz Club]]
'''Herr Nilsen Jazz Club''' is a jazz club in [[Oslo]], [[Norway]]. It is located just to the southeast of the [[Norwegian National Gallery]], just metres north of the [[Hotel Bristol (Oslo)|Hotel Bristol]] and [[Oslo Nye Teater]], overlooking the courthouse square. [[Darwin Porter]] of [[Frommer's]] describes the club as "one of the most congenial spots in Oslo and a personal favorite."<ref name="Porter2009">{{cite book|last=Porter|first=Darwin|title=Frommer's Norway|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FiYdnOs4hB0C&pg=PA163|accessdate=7 December 2011|date=1 May 2009|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-0-470-43213-6|page=163}}</ref> It often hosts internationally and nationally famous jazz musicians, with a focus on [[Dixieland]] jazz music of [[New Orleans]].

