{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
[[Image:Jaroslav Borzita of Martinice.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Jaroslav Borzita of Martinice]]
'''Jaroslav Bořita z Martinic''' ({{IPA-cs|ˈjaroslav ˈbor̝ɪta}}; {{Lang-de|Jaroslav Borsita von Martinic/Martinitz}}) (6 January 1582 – 21 November 1649) was a [[Czechs|Czech]] nobleman and a representative of [[Ferdinand II, Holy Roman Emperor]] who, along with [[Vilém Slavata of Chlum]], was a victim in the 1618 [[Defenestrations of Prague|Defenestration of Prague]] (also known as the ''Second Defenestration of Prague'').

His daughter Barbara Eusebia was the second wife of [[Christian William of Brandenburg]].

