[[File:Mileştii Mici (3944427747).jpg|thumb|250px|Mileștii Mici has the world's biggest [[wine cellars]].]] [[File:Wine fountain at Milestii Mici (193872576).jpg|thumb|250px|Wine fountain at Mileștii Mici]] '''Mileștii Mici''' is a [[Moldovan wine producers|Moldovan wine producer]] located in the commune of [[Mileștii Mici]].
== Cellars == The State Enterprise Quality Wines Industrial Complex "Mileștii Mici" was founded in 1969 to store, preserve and mature high-quality wines.
Local ancient underground galleries reach the [[Chişinău]] borders. The limestone in the galleries maintains constant humidity (85–95%) and temperature ({{convert|12|–|14|C|F|lk=on|disp=sqbr}})<ref name=eco>{{cite web|last=Spânu |first=Vlad |title=Cricova: The Largest Underground Wine Cellar in the World |url=http://economie.moldova.org/news/cricova-the-largest-underground-wine-cellar-in-the-world-19083-eng.html |publisher=economie.moldova.org |accessdate=8 September 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120902060521/http://economie.moldova.org/news/cricova-the-largest-underground-wine-cellar-in-the-world-19083-eng.html |archivedate=2 September 2012 |df= }}</ref> throughout the year. The longer some specific [[red wine]]s are stored in such ideal conditions, the more they improve. Some wines are cellared for several decades before being sold. The cellars extend for {{convert|200|km}}, of which only {{convert|55|km}} are currently in use.
In August 2005, Mileștii Mici was registered in the [[Guinness World Records]] as the biggest wine collection in the world.<ref>[http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/largest-wine-cellar-by-number-of-bottles/ Largest wine cellar by number of bottles] guinnessworldrecords.com</ref> Overall, the complex holds nearly 2 million bottles.<ref name="eco"/> More than 70% of the stored wines are red, 20% are white and about 10% are dessert wines. The most valuable items of this collection, worth €480 a bottle, were produced in 1973–74; they are now exported only to Japan.
Wines are exported from Mileștii Mici to Sweden, Japan, the USA, Great Britain, the Czech Republic, Poland, Greece, Germany, Denmark, Finland, and China.
== Wines == The wines stored here are made from crops of various years, beginning with 1969. Grapes include [[Pinot (grape)|Pinot]], [[Traminer]], [[Muscat (grape and wine)|Muscat]], [[Riesling]], [[Dnestrovscoie]], [[Milestscoie]], [[Codru (wine)|Codru]], [[Negru de Purcari]], [[Trandafirul Moldovei]], [[Auriu]], and [[Cahor-Ciumai]].
