===Army=== The army, called the ''Umbutfo Swaziland Defence Force'' (USDF), is the main component of Swaziland's military.<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/wz.html |title=CIA - The World Factbook |publisher=Cia.gov |date= |accessdate=2012-07-06}}</ref>
====Facilities====
* Nsingizini Army Barracks * Mbuluzi Barracks * Mdzimba Mountain Barracks * Phocweni Barracks * Etjeni Barracks * Zombodze Barracks
====Units====
* Ludlukhala Regiment * Lindimpi Regiment (watchman/guard) * Gcina Regiment
===Navy=== Due to Swaziland being landlocked, the country does not maintain a navy.<ref name="autogenerated1"/>
==Commanders==
* 1973–1977: Prince [[Bhekimpi Dhlamini]] (as commander of [[Royal Swaziland Defence Force]])<ref name="issafrica.org">https://www.issafrica.org/uploads/EVOLUTCHAP10.PDF</ref> * 1977–1979: Colonel [[Maphevu Dlamini]] (died in office)<ref name="issafrica.org"/> * 1981: Colonel [[Jameson Ndizimande]] (appointment was later annulled)<ref name="issafrica.org"/> * 1983–2000?: Brigadier [[Gideon Dube]] <ref name="issafrica.org"/> * 2000–present: Major General [[Stanley Dlamini]]
