[[File:Wahlkreis Otjombinde in Omaheke.png|right|thumb|Otjombinde Constituency (yellow) in the Omaheke Region (dark grey)]]
'''Otjombinde Constituency''' is an [[Constituencies of Namibia|electoral constituency]] in the [[Omaheke Region]] of [[Namibia]]. It had 6,378 inhabitants in 2004.<ref>[http://www.statoids.com/yna.html Constituencies of Namibia, 2004]</ref> The district capital of the constituency is the settlement of [[Otjombinde]], its main economic hub is [[Talismanus]].<ref>{{Cite news | title=Nguvauva wants Eiseb Block to be declared a constituency | newspaper=[[New Era (Namibia)|New Era]] | date=17 November 2015 | url=https://www.newera.com.na/2015/11/17/nguvauva-eiseb-block-declared-constituency/}}</ref> The constituency forms part of the border between Namibia and [[Botswana]], it contains the settlements of [[Eiseb]],<ref>{{Cite news | title=Du Plessis-Epukiro road upgrade next financial year | newspaper=[[The Namibian]] | date=30 January 2018 | page=6| url=https://www.namibian.com.na/63828/read/Du-Plessis-Epukiro-road-upgrade-next-financial-year}}</ref> [[Helena, Namibia|Helena]], and [[Rietfontein, Omaheke|Rietfontein]].<ref>{{cite news | publisher = Electoral Commission of Namibia | title = Presidential and National Assembly Elections 2009 | work = Supplement to several Namibian newspapers | date = November 2009}}</ref>
The constituency is inhabited by [[Ovambanderu]] and [[San people]]. San settlements include [[Donkerbos]] and [[Sonneblom]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.az.com.na/politik/keine-sichtbaren-zeichen-von-hunger-and-quot.6512.php |title=Keine sichtbaren Zeichen von Hunger |trans-title=No visible signs of starvation |language=German |date=1 December 2003 |work=[[Allgemeine Zeitung (Namibia)|Allgemeine Zeitung]]}}</ref>
==Politics== The [[Namibian local and regional elections, 2015|2015 regional election]] was won by [[Katjanna Kaurivi]], an [[independent candidate]], with 1,396 votes. Karri Marenga of the [[South West Africa People's Organization|SWAPO Party]] finished second with 681 votes, followed by Jeremiah Ndjoze of the [[South West Africa National Union]] (SWANU) with 267 votes and Lukas Katjiremba of the [[Democratic Turnhalle Alliance]] (DTA) with 134 votes.<ref>{{Cite web | title=Regional Council Election Results 2015 | publisher=[[Electoral Commission of Namibia]] | date=3 December 2015 | page=16 | url=http://www.ecn.na/documents/27857/223442/Regional+Counils+Election+Results_Duly+elected+candidates+2015.pdf/32493774-80b3-4be3-9ca1-1f6ce187673a?version=1.0 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208163948/http://www.ecn.na/documents/27857/223442/Regional+Counils+Election+Results_Duly+elected+candidates+2015.pdf/32493774-80b3-4be3-9ca1-1f6ce187673a?version=1.0 | archivedate=8 December 2015 | df= }}</ref>
